Seldon R. GLENN, Collector of Internal Revenue for the District of Kentucky, v. A. D. REYNOLDS, Jr., and Grace Reynolds. No. 7162. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 7, 1936. Bunk Gardner, U. S. Atty., of Louisville, Ky., for appellant. Woodward, Dawson & Hobson and Edward P. Humphrey, all of Louisville, Ky., for appellees.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed pursuant to motion of appellees.
